It was a selloff day on the #DOW , but this still turned out to be its best week since 1938! After Trump signs that relief bill, it will probably set up another rally. But who can predict the #stockmarkets these days?

Despite a late session air pocket that saw the #Dow close down over 900 points (4.1%), its weekly performance was the best since 1938. In the process, it reduced the year-to-date loss to 24.1%. The #risk -off tone took the yield on the 10-year US government #bonds below 0.70%. https:// twitter.com/elerianm/statu s/1243615617086705664 …
